
1. A student passes an exam only if they score 35 marks or above. Write a program to determine whether the student has passed or failed.


2. A person can vote only if they are 18 years old or above. Write a program to check voting eligibility.


3. A customer receives a 10% discount if their shopping bill exceeds ₹5000. Write a program to calculate the final amount.


4. A user can access a website only if the entered password matches the stored password. Write a program to verify the password.


5. Based on marks, assign grades:

90–100 → A

75–89 → B

50–74 → C

Below 50 → Fail



6. Create a simple calculator that performs addition, subtraction, multiplication, or division based on the user's choice.


7. Calculate electricity charges based on units consumed:

0–100 units → ₹2/unit

101–200 units → ₹3/unit

Above 200 units → ₹5/unit



8. Determine the ticket fare based on age:

Below 5 years → Free

5–12 years → ₹50

Above 12 years → ₹100



9. A bank approves a loan only if the applicant's salary is above ₹30,000. If eligible, check whether their credit score is above 700 before approving the loan.


10. A student is eligible for college admission only if they have scored above 60% in academics. If eligible, check whether their entrance exam score is above 70.


11. A company recruits candidates only if their degree percentage is above 65%. If eligible, check whether their aptitude test score is above 75.


12. A scholarship is awarded only if a student scores above 80%. If eligible, check whether their attendance is above 75%.


13. An ATM should allow cash withdrawal only if the account balance is sufficient. If sufficient, verify the user's PIN before processing the transaction.


14. A secure login system should first verify the username, then the password, and finally an OTP before granting access.


15. A hospital appointment can be confirmed only if the doctor is available. If available, check whether appointment slots are still open.


16. A student can access the cybersecurity lab only if they are registered. If registered, verify whether the course fees have been paid.


17. An employee is eligible for a bonus only if they have more than 3 years of experience. If eligible, check whether their performance rating is 8 or above.


18. An online examination portal should allow access only if the hall ticket is available. If available, verify whether all fees have been cleared.


19. A hostel room can be allotted only if the student has been selected for admission. If selected, check whether rooms are available.


20. An online shopping website offers:

20% discount for premium members if the purchase amount exceeds ₹5000.

10% discount for non-premium members if the purchase amount exceeds ₹5000.

No discount otherwise. Write a program to determine the discount.